From 5407a8c65eabe70df9c05479eaf23a73bffa9cb3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: lhl <lhl@randomfoo.net>
Date: Thu, 12 Mar 2026 05:34:40 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] media: i2c: ov5675: Reorder supplies for power sequencing

On TPS68470-based platforms the VSIO regulator controls the sensor-side
I2C bus. Enabling VSIO (dovdd) before the sensor core supply (dvdd) can
lead to transaction timeouts on the shared PMIC bus.

Reorder the supply array so that regulator_bulk_enable() powers the
rails in the order avdd -> dvdd -> dovdd, matching the sequencing
observed on working systems. regulator_bulk_disable() already tears
down in reverse array order, which gives the corresponding dovdd ->
dvdd -> avdd power-off sequence.

Signed-off-by: lhl <lhl@randomfoo.net>
---
 drivers/media/i2c/ov5675.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/media/i2c/ov5675.c b/drivers/media/i2c/ov5675.c
index 2b7c5abe6f73..ab730e04ac5c 100644
--- a/drivers/media/i2c/ov5675.c
+++ b/drivers/media/i2c/ov5675.c
@@ -83,8 +83,8 @@
 
 static const char * const ov5675_supply_names[] = {
 	"avdd",		/* Analog power */
-	"dovdd",	/* Digital I/O power */
 	"dvdd",		/* Digital core power */
+	"dovdd",	/* Digital I/O power */
 };
 
 #define OV5675_NUM_SUPPLIES	ARRAY_SIZE(ov5675_supply_names)
